With the vectors $\mathbf{p}$ and $\mathbf{q}$ defined in Lemma~\ref{lemma:long-vector}, we have $\mathbf{p}^{\rm H}\mathbf{p}=\sum_{k=1}^{n}a_k|p_k|^2$ and $\mathbb{E}\left\{\mathbf{p}^{\rm H}\mathbf{p}\right\}=\sum_{k=1}^{n}a_{k}\mu_{p, k}$. Let $z$ be a constant which satisfies \eqref{app_eq:long-vector-1_condition}. It is then clear that $\mathrm{Var}\left\{|a_i^{\frac{1}{2}}p_i|^2\right\}=|a_i|^2\sigma^2_{p, i} < \infty$. Therefore, by applying the well-known law of large numbers for \ac{i.n.i.d.} \acp{RV} \cite[p. 313]{Grinstead2012} to $a_i^{\frac{1}{2}}p_i$, the entries of $\mathbf{p}$, \eqref{app_eq:long-vector_convergence-1} is easily attained.

